data.title: Supported Products and Versions
data.meta_description: vRealize Network Insight supports several VMware and third party products and their different versions.
data.text:
vRealize Network Insight supports several VMware and third party products and their different versions.

For the list of all VMware products and its supported versions in vRealize Network Insight, see VMware Product Interoperability Matrices.

The following table lists all the third party devices and its associated operating systems supported in vRealize Network Insight.

Data Source Version/Model

Supported Operating System (OS) and Versions

Supports Network Assurance and Verification feature (Network Map and Intents)

New OS Versions Certification Frequency**

Note:

** Shows the frequency at which VMware certifies the compatibility of vRealize Network Insight version with the new OS versions of supported third-party devices. This timeline is based on the availability of the device.

*** vRealize Network Insight does not support Active-Active FEX (VPC) configuration for Cisco Nexus 2000 in Network Assurance and Verification.

In addition to the mentioned supported major OS versions, vRealize Network Insight supports all the minor releases associated with these major releases.

In addition to the devices mentioned in the table, the following VMware products also supports Network Assurance and Verification feature (Network Map and Intents) in the latest version of vRealize Network Insight:

VMware NSX-T Manager

Distributed and Edge firewall

Multiple VTEPs

VMware vCenter

VMware vSphere Distributed Switch (VDS)

You can get information about the required ports for all data sources supported in vRealize Network Insight at VMware Ports and Protocols.

For third-party devices such as switches, routers, and firewalls, vRealize Network Insight uses SSH connections for fetching the configuration data. To learn about supported algorithms for such SSH connections, see Encryption Algorithms and Ciphers.
